name: ethanedione, di-2-furanyl-, dioxime
Reason: 1,2-furanyl groups can add approximately +20 due to the increase in molecular weight and rigidity of the structure. The dioxime group introduces additional rigid structures that can participate in dipole interactions, raising the melting point by about +30. The ethanedione base itself has a melting point around 50 degrees Celsius.
